<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-27T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="251" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Y2/22a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>291. Reported in press that German Government has stated that <hi rend="italic">Yarrowdale</hi> prisoners can not be released owing to
                            breaking out <pb facs="0384" n="212" xml:id="pg_212"/> among them of an
                            infectious disease. Ask Spanish Government to instruct Ambassador to
                            ascertain if statement is true and request permission to send
                            representative of Spanish Embassy to make investigation and report
                            actual condition of men. Owing to seemingly unnecessary delay in the
                            release of these men there is a growing feeling of irritation. Hope this
                            matter can be taken up promptly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>